[1] South Africa
Date: Tue 9 Dec 2014
Source: Longevity Live [edited]
http://www.longevitylive.com/healthy-and-happy/health-living/alert-measles-outbreak-across-sa/


South Africa has recorded a surge in measles cases, with the Northern Cape Province topping the list, warned the National Institute for Communicable Diseases. "Over the past 2 months, there has been an increase in laboratory-confirmed (IgM positive) measles cases." The 5 provinces affected are Gauteng, Mpumalanga, KwaZulu-Natal, Northern Cape and Western Cape.

Sporadic laboratory-confirmed measles cases have also been noted in the Eastern Cape and Free State. "No laboratory-confirmed measles cases have been reported from Limpopo and Northwest provinces during 2014 to date."

The National Institute for Communicable Diseases says you should look out for these signs:

- High fever, rising over 3 days to 39 to 40.5 C [102-104.9 F]
- Runny nose
- A harsh, dry cough
- Red, inflamed eyes (conjunctivitis) and aversion to bright light

[Byline: Siyanda Nkala]

